ðŸ“Œ C++ programming mein, syntax ek set of rules hai jo aapko C++ programming code likhne ke liye follow karna hoga. C++ programming mein, syntax ke rules define karte hai ki kaise variable declare karte hai, kaise functions define aur call karte hai aur kaise control structures use karte hai.

ðŸ“Œ C++ programming mein, syntax ko follow karne se aapko code likhne mein help milta hai aur code ka execution time aur memory ka use kam hota hai.

ðŸ“Œ C++ programming mein, syntax ke kuch important rules hai:

ðŸ“ 1: C++ programming mein, code ko semicolon (;) ke saath end karne chahiye.

Example:

int a;   // Correct
int a; // Incorrect

ðŸ“ 2: C++ programming mein, functions ka return type define karne chahiye.

Example:

int add(int a, int b) { // Correct
    return a + b;
}
void add(int a, int b) { // Incorrect
    return a + b;

ðŸ“ 3: C++ programming mein, variables ko declare karne se pehle, data types define karne chahiye.

Example:

int a; // Correct
a = 10;

int; // Incorrect
a = 10;

ðŸ“ 4: C++ programming mein, comments ko double slash (//) ya /* */ ke saath shuru karte hai aur end karte hai.

Example:

// This is a single line comment
/* This is a
multi-line comment */

ðŸ“ 5: C++ programming mein, string literal ko double quotes ke saath define karte hai.

Example: string str = 'Hello World'; // Correct
string str = 'Hello World'; // Incorrect

ðŸ“ 6: C++ programming mein, keywords ko reserve karte hai.

Example:

int main() { // Correct
    return 0;
}

int Main() { // Incorrect
    return 0;
}

ðŸ“ 7: C++ programming mein, operators ke use se aapko variables aur expressions ko manipulate karne mein help milta hai.

Example:

int a = 10;
int b = 20;
int c = a + b; // Correct
int c = a +; // Incorrect

ðŸ“ 8: C++ programming mein, loops aur conditionals ke use se aapko code ko control karne mein help milta hai.

Example:

int a = 10;
if (a > 5) { // Correct
    cout << "a is greater than 5";
}

int a = 10;
if (a > 5) { // Incorrect
    cout << "a is greater than 5";
    cout << "a is greater than 5";
}

ðŸ“ 9: C++ programming mein, functions ke use se aapko code ko modular aur organized banane mein help karta hai.

int add(int a, int b) { // Correct
    return a + b;
}

int main() {
    int a = 10;
    int b = 20;
    int c = add(a, b);
    return 0;
}

int add(int a, int b) { // Incorrect
    return a + b;
}

int main() {
    int a = 10;
    int b = 20;
    int c = a + b;
    return 0;
}

ðŸ“Œ C++ programming mein, syntax ke rules follow karne se aapko code likhne ka aur debug karne ka maza aata hai.
